      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 198,
      "message": "This should really use the Java classes to retrieve a remote URL. Executing \"curl\" as a subprocess is an extremely expensive way to do this. This is especially true when doing this periodically.\n\ntry {\nURL url = new URL(urlString);\nURLConnection conn = url.openConnection();\nInputStream is = conn.getInputStream();\netc.",
